cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as text classification, sequence labeling, and reading comprehension. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a multi-task learning approach to improve the performance of baseline models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a novel approach to tackle a general issue in NLP tasks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the proposed approach can be applied to image classification tasks as well. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also less likely but possible as the paper mentions the use of distant supervision to retrieve hard-negative examples.
